description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a suitably experienced Biomedical Scientist to provide effective leadership and management to the specialist diagnostic Haematology sections at our Birmingham Women’s and Children’s hospital sites. Our Women’s laboratory provides maternity, neonatal and gynaecology/fertility services and the antenatal Sickle Cell and Thalassaemia (SCT) programme. The Children’s site provide a paediatric and neonatal service including diagnosis of leukaemia, haemoglobinopathies and bleeding disorders plus providing an acute service for ED, Paediatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU) and support of cardiac, liver, burns and bone marrow transplant specialities. Both departments provide a 24/7 laboratory service for our users.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Appointment to Band 8a would require a significant Haematology technical experience together with experience at senior management roles.  The work is interesting and varied and the department encourages and supports career development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews are scheduled for Thursday 19th November 2020 where a presentation will be expected and the topic will be set on the day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further discussion or to arrange an informal visit to the laboratory please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;James Taylor, Head BMS, Blood Sciences, james.taylor7@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
